---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="What is a Ruck Club - Build Your Crew" 
  description="Learn about ruck clubs, why crews matter, and how to build a strong rucking community. Start or join a crew near you."
>
  <div class="bg-surface py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Header Section -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4">RUCK CLUBS</h1>
        <p class="text-lg font-serif text-muted-foreground max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          A ruck club is a crew of individuals who train together, push each other, and build unbreakable bonds through shared adversity.
        </p>
      </div>

    <!-- Why Crews Matter -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Why Crews Matter</h2>
      <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
        <p>
          Rucking is inherently a social activity. While you can ruck alone, joining a crew multiplies the benefits:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>Accountability:</strong> You're less likely to skip a workout when teammates are counting on you.</li>
          <li><strong>Safety in numbers:</strong> Trained crews can handle emergencies, injuries, and unexpected conditions together.</li>
          <li><strong>Progressive overload:</strong> Partners push you to go farther, carry heavier, and train longer than you'd manage alone.</li>
          <li><strong>Shared learning:</strong> Every member brings unique experience—learn from each other's mistakes and successes.</li>
          <li><strong>Camaraderie:</strong> The bonds formed through shared suffering last a lifetime.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Core Principles -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-foreground">Core Principles</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-foreground">Inclusivity</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Welcome individuals of all fitness levels and backgrounds. A strong crew has members at every stage of their rucking journey.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-foreground">Safety</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Prioritize proper form and injury prevention. No PR is worth a trip to the ER.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-foreground">Consistency</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Regular meetings build habit and progress. Show up, stay consistent, and complete the workout.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-foreground">Community</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Foster a supportive and motivating environment. Celebrate every win, big or small.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-foreground">Purpose</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Align rucking with personal and collective goals. Every ruck should have meaning.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-foreground">Growth</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Challenge each other to improve. The goal is progression, not perfection.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Types of Crews -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Types of Ruck Crews</h2>
      <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
        <p>There are many ways to structure a crew. Choose what fits your goals:</p>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Casual Social Crew</h3>
        <p>Meet weekly for conversational-paced rucks. Focus on community and consistency over intensity.</p>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Fitness-Focused Crew</h3>
        <p>Structured training with progressive programming. Members commit to regular attendance and higher intensity.</p>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Competitive Team</h3>
        <p>Train for events, races, or challenges. Higher commitment, structured programming, and performance tracking.</p>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Community Service Crew</h3>
        <p>Combine rucking with volunteer work. Carry supplies for community projects, trail maintenance, or charity events.</p>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Military/Veteran Unit</h3>
        <p>Maintain readiness through rucking. Often includes ruck marches, tactical movements, and unit cohesion training.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Starting Your First Ruck</h2>
      <div class="bg-muted-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-muted-200">
        <ol class="space-y-4 list-decimal list-inside">
          <li class="pl-2">
            <strong>Choose a safe route:</strong> Start with a familiar trail, park path, or neighborhood loop. Know the terrain.
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <strong>Set a reasonable weight:</strong> Beginners should start with 10-20% of body weight. Focus on form first.
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <strong>Establish a meeting point:</strong> Central location with parking. Have a backup plan for bad weather.
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <strong>Communicate expectations:</strong> Tell attendees what to bring, when to arrive, and the planned pace.
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <strong>Keep it simple:</strong> First ruck: 1-2 miles at conversational pace. Coffee afterward is mandatory.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Resources -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-foreground">Resources for Building Your Crew</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <a href="/lead/ruck-clubs/start-a-club" class="block p-6 rounded-lg border border-muted-200 hover:border-primary transition-colors">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-foreground">Start a Club</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Step-by-step guide to launching your crew</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/lead/ruck-clubs/leadership-principles" class="block p-6 rounded-lg border border-muted-200 hover:border-primary transition-colors">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-foreground">Leadership Principles</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Core principles for leading ruck crews</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/lead/ruck-clubs/crew-culture" class="block p-6 rounded-lg border border-muted-200 hover:border-primary transition-colors">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-foreground">Crew Culture</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Building strong crew culture and traditions</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Call to Action -->
    <section class="text-center py-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Ready to Build Your Crew?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-6 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        Start small, stay consistent, and watch your crew grow into something bigger than any individual.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/lead/ruck-clubs/start-a-club" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
          Start a Club
        </a>
        <a href="/lead" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg">
          Back to Leadership
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
